cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.CY, cs.CR, cs.SI 

This paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning techniques to analyze a large corpus of college application essays. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with NLP and related topics. The paper also uses logistic regression, a popular machine learning algorithm, which makes cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. The paper also deals with issues of fairness and bias in college admissions, which could fall under cs.CY (Computers and Society) or cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Finally, the paper uses data auditing to check for potential bias, which could fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
